\title{Full Stack Playbook}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Playbook for full-stack web application missions. Provides guidance on vertical slice milestones, walking skeleton, frontend/backend workers, and quality enforcement. Use for CRUD apps, dashboards, e-commerce sites, and similar projects with distinct frontend and backend layers.}

\subtree{
\title{Full-Stack Web Application Playbook}
\p{This playbook guides you through executing a full-stack web application mission. Use this for CRUD apps, dashboards, e-commerce sites, and similar projects with distinct frontend and backend layers.}

\subtree{
\title{Milestone Strategy: Vertical Slices}
\p{Structure your milestones as \strong{vertical slices} of functionality, not horizontal layers.}

\p{\strong{Good milestones:}}

\ul{
\li{"user-auth" (login, signup, sessions - full stack)}
\li{"product-catalog" (listing, search, detail pages - full stack)}
\li{"checkout" (cart, payment, confirmation - full stack)}
}

\p{\strong{Bad milestones:}}

\ul{
\li{"all-api-endpoints" (horizontal - can't test in isolation)}
\li{"frontend-pages" (horizontal - can't test without backend)}
}

\p{Each milestone should leave the app in a coherent, testable state where a user can complete a meaningful flow.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Walking Skeleton First}
\p{Before any real feature implementation, establish a \strong{walking skeleton} that spans the full user-facing surface with the thinnest possible implementation.}

\p{\strong{Why:} This lets work-scrutiny-validator determine testing needs and user-testing-validator exercise the complete surface from the start. Prevents building features in isolation only to discover integration issues later.}

\p{\strong{What to include:}}

\ul{
\li{All planned UI pages (can be stubs/placeholders)}
\li{All planned API endpoints (can return mock data)}
\li{All planned CLI commands (can be no-ops)}
\li{Basic routing and navigation}
}

\p{\strong{Skeleton milestone should be first.} Once the skeleton exists, subsequent milestones fill in real functionality.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Worker Types for Full-Stack}
\subtree{
\title{frontend-worker}
\ul{
\li{Implements UI features (pages, components, state)}
\li{\strong{TDD: Write component/integration tests FIRST (before any implementation)}}
\li{\strong{MUST do manual browser verification with agent-browser CLI:}}
\li{\strong{Visual quality is essential} - check for:}
\li{Placement and alignment issues}
\li{Z-index problems (overlapping, hidden elements)}
\li{Overflow and content clipping/scroll issues}
\li{Inconsistent margins/padding}
\li{Missing states (hover/focus/disabled/loading/empty/error)}
\li{\strong{Fix issues found:}}
\li{Issues with own work (including from manual testing) → must fix}
\li{Manageable existing issues under their skill → fix them}
\li{Large scope or outside their skill → report to orchestrator}
\li{Include any fixes in whatWasImplemented}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{backend-worker}
\ul{
\li{Implements API endpoints and services}
\li{\strong{TDD: Write API tests FIRST (before any implementation)}}
\li{Verifies actual endpoint behavior (not just tests passing)}
\li{\strong{Fix issues found:}}
\li{Issues with own work (including from manual testing) → must fix}
\li{Manageable existing issues under their skill → fix them}
\li{Large scope or outside their skill → report to orchestrator}
\li{Include any fixes in whatWasImplemented}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quality Enforcement Flow}
\pre{\startverb
1. Orchestrator creates implementation features grouped by milestone
2. Implementation workers build features (TDD + manual verification)
3. When milestone X completes → system injects work-scrutiny-validator
4. Work-scrutiny validates handoffs match diffs, re-runs tests
5. Work-scrutiny determines what user testing is needed and creates testing features
6. User-testing validates user flows via browser (if UI) or appropriate surface
7. Failed validation surfaces bugs → orchestrator creates fix features
8. Repeat until milestone passes, then move to next milestone
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Pitfalls}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Building backend without frontend} - Leads to API designs that don't match UI needs. Build vertical slices instead.}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Skipping the skeleton} - Causes integration issues late in the mission. Always start with skeleton.}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Features too large} - "Build the product page" is too big. Break into: "product list", "product detail", "product search", etc.}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Forgetting error states} - Workers often implement happy path only. expectedBehavior should include error cases.}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Not testing cross-feature interactions} - Login affects what's visible in the catalog. Test these connections.}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{No lasting test infrastructure} - Per-worker TDD produces unit/integration tests, but consider whether the mission also needs dedicated features for shared test fixtures, seed data, or e2e test suites - especially when building on an existing codebase that already has e2e coverage.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example Milestone Breakdown}
\p{For an e-commerce app:}

\p{\strong{Milestone: skeleton}}

\ul{
\li{Stub all routes (home, catalog, product, cart, checkout, auth)}
\li{Stub all API endpoints}
\li{Basic navigation between pages}
}

\p{\strong{Milestone: user-auth}}

\ul{
\li{Login page + endpoint}
\li{Signup page + endpoint}
\li{Session management}
\li{Protected route handling}
}

\p{\strong{Milestone: product-catalog}}

\ul{
\li{Product list page + endpoint}
\li{Product detail page + endpoint}
\li{Product search + filtering}
}

\p{\strong{Milestone: checkout}}

\ul{
\li{Cart management (add, remove, update quantity)}
\li{Checkout flow (shipping, payment)}
\li{Order confirmation}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example: backend-worker Skill}
\pre{\startverb
---
name: backend-worker
description: Implement backend features including API endpoints, services, and business logic.
---

# Backend Worker

## When to Use This Skill

Features involving API endpoints, backend services, database operations, or server-side logic.

## Work Procedure

### 1. Understand the Feature

Read the feature's description, expectedBehavior, and preconditions.
Identify endpoints/services to create, input/output shapes, and error cases.

### 2. Write Tests First (TDD)

Before implementing, write tests that define expected behavior:

- API tests: request/response shapes, status codes, error responses
- Unit tests: service logic, edge cases

Run tests - they should fail (red).

### 3. Implement

Write minimum code to make tests pass. Follow patterns in AGENTS.md.
Run tests - they should pass (green).

### 4. Manual Verification

Tests passing isn't enough. Actually call the endpoints:

- Make real HTTP requests (curl, httpie, or similar)
- Test error cases manually
- Check logs for unexpected errors

### 5. Fix Issues Found

- Issues with your own work (including from manual verification) → must fix
- Manageable existing issues that fall under your skill → fix them
- Large scope issues or outside your skill → report to orchestrator in discoveredIssues

Include any fixes in whatWasImplemented.

### 6. Run Verification Steps

Execute each step in the feature's verificationSteps array.

## Handoff Requirements

Use the EndFeatureRun tool with structured handoff. Here's what thorough work looks like:

### Example Handoff (Product Search Endpoint)

\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
{ "whatWasImplemented": "GET /api/products/search endpoint with query parameter, relevance sorting, pagination via cursor, and input validation requiring minimum 2-character queries. Also fixed existing bug in GET /api/products/:id that was returning soft-deleted products.", "whatWasLeftUndone": "", "verification": { "commandsRun": [ { "command": "npm test -- --grep 'product search'", "exitCode": 0, "observation": "4 tests passed: 'returns matching products sorted by relevance', 'returns empty array for no matches', 'paginates with cursor', 'rejects query under 2 chars'" }, { "command": "curl 'http://localhost:3000/api/products/search?q=wireless+headphones&limit=5'", "exitCode": 0, "observation": "returned 5 products, first was Sony WH-1000XM5 with score 0.94, response included cursor eyJvZmZzZXQiOjV9" }, { "command": "curl 'http://localhost:3000/api/products/search?q=xyznonexistent'", "exitCode": 0, "observation": "returned {\"results\":[],\"message\":\"No products found matching 'xyznonexistent'\"}" }, { "command": "curl 'http://localhost:3000/api/products/search?q=a'", "exitCode": 0, "observation": "returned 400 with {\"error\":\"Query must be at least 2 characters\",\"code\":\"INVALID_QUERY\"}" } ], "interactiveChecks": [] }, "tests": { "added": [ { "file": "tests/api/product-search.test.ts", "cases": [ { "name": "returns matching products sorted by relevance", "verifies": "basic search returns results ordered by score descending" }, { "name": "returns empty array with message for no matches", "verifies": "graceful handling when nothing matches query" }, { "name": "paginates results with cursor", "verifies": "cursor-based pagination for large result sets" }, { "name": "returns 400 for query under 2 characters", "verifies": "input validation rejects too-short queries" } ] } ], "coverage": "search query handling, relevance sorting, pagination, input validation, empty results" }, "discoveredIssues": [ { "severity": "suggestion", "description": "Response time ~800ms for common terms like 'phone' - requires DB indexing or caching layer (outside feature scope)", "suggestedFix": "Consider adding search index or caching layer" } ] }
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb

## When to Return to Orchestrator

- Requirements are ambiguous or contradictory
- Existing bugs affect this feature
- Scope is larger than expected (e.g., requires unmentioned migration)
- Design decision affects other features
\stopverb}
}
}
}